    <title>Placement-ABC</title>
    <link href="http://yoursite.com/2020/01/28/placement-ABC/"/>
    <id>http://yoursite.com/2020/01/28/placement-ABC/</id>
    <published>2020-01-28T03:01:06.000Z</published>
    <updated>2020-01-28T08:52:25.800Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<link rel="stylesheet" class="aplayer-secondary-style-marker" href="/assets/css/APlayer.min.css"><script src="/assets/js/APlayer.min.js" class="aplayer-secondary-script-marker"></script><p>Bored to death, Jan. 28, 2020, due to the outbreak of Wuhan coronavirus and the restricted travel.</p><p>Some basics of back-end designs, including Placement on ASIC and FPGA.</p><p>[TOC]</p><h2 id="VLSI-Design-Cycle">VLSI Design Cycle</h2><p>System Specification $\rightarrow$ Architecture Design $\rightarrow$ Functional Design.</p><a id="more"></a><h2 id="ePlace-MS">ePlace-MS</h2><blockquote><p>ePlace-MS Electrostatics-Based Placement for Mixed-Size Circuits</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>2015 TCAD</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>generalized, analytic and nonlinear, for large-scale mixed-size circuits.</p></blockquote><ol><li>Nesterov’s method</li><li>backtracking method to prevent overestimation</li><li>nonlinear preconditioner</li><li>simulated annealer legalization</li><li>second-phase global placement (re-optimize)</li></ol><script>        document.querySelectorAll('.github-emoji')          .forEach(el => {            if (!el.dataset.src) { return; }            const img = document.createElement('img');            img.style = 'display:none !important;';            img.src = el.dataset.src;            img.addEventListener('error', () => {              img.remove();              el.style.color = 'inherit';              el.style.backgroundImage = 'none';              el.style.background = 'none';            });            img.addEventListener('load', () => {              img.remove();            });            document.body.appendChild(img);          });      </script>]]></content>
    
    <summary type="html">
    
      &lt;p&gt;Bored to death, Jan. 28, 2020, due to the outbreak of Wuhan coronavirus and the restricted travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some basics of back-end designs, including Placement on ASIC and FPGA.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[TOC]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;VLSI-Design-Cycle&quot;&gt;VLSI Design Cycle&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;System Specification $\rightarrow$ Architecture Design $\rightarrow$ Functional Design.&lt;/p&gt;
    
    </summary>
    
    
